                {
                  "key": "response",
                  "value": {
                    "stringValue": "Implemented all three stories of epic **APA-43342** (Sparkathon demo additions):\n\n**Story A — Consolidated session report** (`extractor/consolidate.py`, `APA-43347`): collapses consecutive `records.csv` rows into one row per unbroken run of Model/Agent/Skills/JIRA Key, with sum aggregation and a CLI (`python -m extractor.consolidate`).\n\n**Story B — JIRA resume map** (`extractor/jira_map.py`, `APA-43343`): derives a `session_id → last JIRA key` snapshot from `records.csv`, wired into `correlate.py`/`cli.py` so a session resumed after `.state/` loss still gets correctly attributed.\n\n**Story C — Interval scheduling** (`extractor/cli.py`, `APA-43345`): new `--interval SECONDS` flag runs the extractor in a loop with a clean `Ctrl+C` exit; refactored the one-shot body into a testable `run_once`/`run_interval`.\n\n**Story D — Handoff docs**: `HANDOFF_consolidation.md`, `HANDOFF_jira_resume_map.md`, `HANDOFF_interval_scheduling.md` at repo root.\n\nAll 43 tests pass (`python -m pytest tests/ -v`), including 20 new tests across the three stories, plus a manual dry-run against the real `received/` sample data (80 records → 6 consolidated groups; JIRA map correctly seeded and survived a `.state/` wipe). One caveat noted in the interval-scheduling handoff: I couldn't cleanly verify the `Ctrl+C` exit path via a real terminal signal in this Windows/Git-Bash sandbox (signal delivery quirk, not a code issue) — the automated test covers that exact code path instead.\n\nNothing has been committed — let me know if you'd like these changes committed/pushed."
